🧾 Spring Data JPA – Custom Query using @Query (SCN Format)

1. 🧠 Concept
@Query is used in Spring Data JPA to define custom queries manually when derived query methods are not enough.
👉 Supports:
JPQL (Entity-based)
Native SQL (Table-based)

2. ⚙️ Core Syntax
🔹 JPQL (Default)
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.name = :name")
User findByName(@Param("name") String name);

🔹 Native SQL
@Query(value = "SELECT * FROM user_table WHERE name = ?1", nativeQuery = true)
User findUser(String name);


3. 📌 Rules for @Query

🔹 1. JPQL Uses Entity Names (NOT table names)
❌ Wrong:
SELECT * FROM user_table

✅ Correct:
SELECT u FROM User u


🔹 2. Use Entity Field Names (NOT column names)
❌ Wrong:
WHERE user_name = :name

✅ Correct:
WHERE u.name = :name


🔹 3. Parameter Binding
✔ Named Parameters
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.email = :email")
User getByEmail(@Param("email") String email);

✔ Positional Parameters
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.email = ?1")
User getByEmail(String email);


🔹 4. SELECT Queries Return Matching Type
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u")
List<User> findAllUsers();


🔹 5. UPDATE / DELETE Needs @Modifying
@Modifying
@Query("UPDATE User u SET u.name = :name WHERE u.id = :id")
void updateName(@Param("id") Long id, @Param("name") String name);


🔹 6. Use @Transactional for Modifying Queries
@Transactional
@Modifying
@Query("DELETE FROM User u WHERE u.id = :id")
void deleteUser(Long id);


🔹 7. Native Query When Using SQL
@Query(value = "SELECT * FROM user_table WHERE age > ?1", nativeQuery = true)
List<User> findByAge(int age);


🔹 8. Alias is Mandatory in JPQL
SELECT u FROM User u


4. 🚀 Approach
Decide JPQL or Native SQL
Write query using entity or table
Bind parameters (:name or ?1)
Add @Modifying if update/delete
Ensure correct return type

5. 💻 Examples
@Query("SELECT p FROM Product p WHERE p.price > :price")
List<Product> getExpensiveProducts(@Param("price") double price);

@Query(value = "SELECT * FROM product_table WHERE title = ?1", nativeQuery = true)
List<Product> findByTitle(String title);


6. 🎯 Key Points
@Query = custom SQL/JPQL
JPQL → entity-based
Native → table-based
Use @Modifying for update/delete
Use @Param for named binding
Prefer JPQL unless SQL is required

7. 📌 Learnings
Use derived queries for simple logic
Use @Query for complex filtering
Most interview mistakes = mixing table vs entity names
Always match return type with query result


